00M<ref>{{cite news |title=Biotechnology: The start-up engine|author=Heidi Ledford|url=http://www.nature.com/news/biotechnology-the-start-up-engine-1.13802|newspaper=[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]|date=25 September 2013|accessdate=26 September 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n! [[Toba Capital]]\n| [[Newport Beach, California]]\n| 2012\n| Vinnie Smith\n| Software and technology services\n| $35M (2016)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ocbj.com/news/2017/jun/05/top-vc-firms-invest-47-more-local-companies/ |title=Top VC Firms Invest 47% More in Local Companies |website=ocbj.com |date=2017-06-05 |accessdate=2018-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n! [[Union Square Ventures]]\n| [[New York City]]\n| 2005\n| [[Fred Wilson (financier)|Fred Wilson]], Brad Burnham, Albert Wenger, John Buttrick, Andy Weissman\n| Technology\n|\n|-\n! [[U.S. Venture Partners]]\n| [[Menlo Park, California]]<ref name=\"usvp.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.usvp.com/|title=Home|author=|date=|website=USVP/|access-date=30 April 2019}}</ref>\n| 1981<ref name=\"usvp.com\"/>\n| Irwin Federman, Winston Fu, Steve Krausz, Paul Matteucci, Jonathan Root, Casey Tansey, Mamoon Hamid, Alan Kaganov, Larry Lasky, Rick Lewis, Ted Maidenberg, Chris Rust, Geoffrey Baehr, Jacques Benkoski, John Hadl, David Liddle, Phil Schlein, Phil Young<ref name=\"usvp.com\"/>\n| Energy-related products and services, semiconductors, Web-enabled services, storage, wireless communication, sustainable agriculture, biomedical devices and new drugs<ref name=\"usvp.com\"/>\n| $2,700 M<ref name=\"usvp.com\"/>\n|-\n! [[VantagePoint Venture Partners]]\n| [[San Bruno, California]]\n| 1996\n| [[Alan E. Salzman]], Jim Marver\n| Cleantech, information technology, healthcare\n| $4,500 M\n|-\n! [[Venrock]]\n| [[Palo Alto, California]]<ref name=\"venrock.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.venrock.com/|title=Home|author=|date=|website=Venrock|access-date=30 April 2019}}</ref>\n| 1969<ref name=\"venrock.com\"/>\n|Brian Ascher, Fred Aslan, Mike Brooks, Marissa Campise, Tony Evnin, Steve Goldberg, Steve Goldby, Anders Hove, Bob Kocher, Bong Koh, Spencer Maughan, Matthew M.Nordan, David Pakman, Bruce Pasternack, [[William Rastetter]], Bryan Roberts, Gur Roshwalb, Ray Rothrock, Matthew Trevithick, Mike Tyrrell<ref name=\"venrock.com\"/>\n| Information technology, healthcare and energy<ref name=\"venrock.com\"/>\n| $2,600 M<ref name=\"venrock.com\"/>\n|-\n! [[Viola Ventures]]\n| [[Herzliya]]\n| 2000\n| [[Shlomo Dovrat]], Avi Zeevi, Rina Shainski, Ori Bendori, Ronen Nir\n| Software, Internet, Networking and Wireless technologies\n| $620 M<ref name=Dun>{{Citation\n | title = Dun's 100 2009 \u2014 Venture Capital Funds\n | url = http://duns100.dundb.co.il/ts.cgi?tsscript=/2009e/e55a10\n | journal = Dun & Bradstreet Israel Ltd.\n | access-date = November 11, 2012\n | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120310165714/http://duns100.dundb.co.il/ts.cgi?tsscript=%2F2009e%2Fe55a10\n | archive-date = March 10, 2012\n | url-status = dead\n }}</ref>\n|-\n! [[Wellington Partners Venture Capital]]\n| [[Munich]]\n| 1991\n| Rolf Christof Dienst, Frank B\u00f6hnke\n| Technology, Digital Media, Life Sciences\n| $700 M under management<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wellington-partners.com|title=Wellington Partners Venture Capital|first=Wellington Partners Venture|last=Capital|website=www.wellington-partners.com}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Noosphere Ventures]]\n|[[Menlo Park, California|Menlo Park, Californi]]\n|2014\n|Partners. Max Polyakov - Managing Partner, Mark Watt - Consultant\n|Space\n|Assets under management\u00a0 $150-170 M\n|}\n\n==Assets under management and dry powder==\nShown below are the largest venture capital firms by AUM and dry powder from 2007 - 2017 from the Preqin Venture Report. <ref>{{cite press release|title=Preqin Special Report: The Venture Capital Top 100}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 85%\" width= align=\n|- style=\"background:lightgrey;\"\n!Rank||Firm||Headquarters||10-Year Capital Raised ($MM)||Dry Powder ($MM)\n|-\n|1